        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 4:33PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 432 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles south of Mammoth Lakes. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Thomas Edison, Kaiser Point, High Sierra, Volcanic Knob, and
Florence Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
